// Description: This script generates a 2D spline using a set of control points defined by the user.
// Author: Tim Olson
// Date :2025-09-07
//Notes:  This is a basic example demonstrating how to use the Spline function.

// ---------------- Setup ----------------
Units(1[mm]);          // Keep scale predictable across drawings
Input();               // Stand-alone part (no external parameters)

// ---------------- Control Points (8 unique) ----------------
// Tip: Keep Z=0 for a planar 2D spline in the XY plane.
P0 = ParameterPoint(  0,  0, 0);
P1 = ParameterPoint( 10,  5, 0);
P2 = ParameterPoint( 20,  3, 0);
P3 = ParameterPoint( 30,  8, 0);
P4 = ParameterPoint( 40, -2, 0);
P5 = ParameterPoint( 50,  0, 0);
P6 = ParameterPoint( 60,  7, 0);
P7 = ParameterPoint( 70,  2, 0);

// ---------------- Spline ----------------
// Direct-call form with eight point arguments (no Array).
Spline2D = Spline(P0, P1, P2, P3, P4, P5, P6, P7);

// ---------------- Output ----------------
Output(Spline2D);      // Output the curve to the drawing
